AC  GenProp0061
DE  lipoprotein system lgt/lsp/lnt
TP  SYSTEM
AU  Haft D
TH  0
CC  YES  NO    Some membrane proteins are anchored to the membrane by a
CC  lipid moiety attached to a modified N-terminus rather than by a
CC  transmembrane helix. The characteristic enzymes of this modification
CC  system are  lsp: prolipoprotein signal peptidase  lgt: prolipoprotein
CC  diacylglycerol transferase  lnt: apolipoprotein N-acyltransferase  The
CC  modifications are cleavage (by Lsp) of the lipoprotein signal sequence
CC  at a motif resembling L-X-G/A-C to leave Cys as the new N-terminal
CC  residue, then modification of the Cys sulfhydryl by prolipoprotein
CC  diacylglyceryl transferase (Lgt), then acylation of the Cys NH2 by
CC  apolipoprotein N-acyltransferase (Lnt).
--
